-- Japanese Bought Net 1542.4 Billion Yen Overseas Debt Last Week
-- B y   I s a a c   A q u i n o
-- 2012-10-03T23:53:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-03/japanese-bought-net-1542-4-billion-yen-overseas-debt-last-week.html
Japanese investors were net
buyers of foreign bonds during the week ended Sept. 28 according
to figures based on reports from designated major investors
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors bought 1542.4 billion yen ($19.7 billion)
in overseas bonds and notes, sold 0.9 billion yen in overseas stocks
and bought 31 billion yen in overseas short term securities.
That results in a total net purchase of 1572.6 billion yen.  Foreign investors bought 298 billion yen in Japanese bonds,
sold 239.6 billion yen in stocks, and bought 34.2 billion yen in
short term securities, resulting in a total net purchase of 92.7
billion yen.    To contact the reporter on this story:
Isaac Aquino in Tokyo at   iaquino1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
